UNITED STATES of America, Appellee, v. Clark W. PARKER and Wyman C. Parker, Appellants. No. 425. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 6, 1932. Harry Kopp, of New York City (Jerome G. Rosenhaus, of New York City, of counsel), for Wyman C. Parker. John A. Bolles, of New York City (Edwin L. La Crosse, of New York City, of' counsel), for Clark W. Parker. George Z. Medalie, U. S. Atty., of New York City (J. Edward Lumbard, Jr., Bernard Tompkins, and Curtiss E. Frank, Asst., U. S. Attys., all, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, AUGUSTUS N, HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
